rComments: Dr. Ouimet is so knowledgeable and clearly is an expert in what shes talking about. Shes also very accessible to students, and really does want you to succeed. She also uses her personal experience to make the lectures more interesting. I cant recommend her enough!

One of my favourite profs! Her lectures were interesting and went by so quickly! There are 2 midterms (20% and 30%) and a final. There are 7 mini in-class assignments but they can often be done in groups. Her exams are super fair, they are 75% lecture material and 25% textbook material. She was pretty much the highlight of my semester. Take her!!!!

Such a kind professor. She really makes this already interesting class more interesting, and knows her stuff! I found myself going to lectures because I genuinely enjoyed myself there. Would recommend taking a class with her

She cares about making a difference when it comes to stigma, which is incredible. She has good examples and conveys the material effectively. She also encourages participation but doesn't put anyone on the spot. Overall, she's a great professor--I definitely recommend her.

Really engaging and young prof, makes you excited to attend class. Attendance is mandatory because she does random in-class assignments. Lots of readingit. She's fun to listen to, hilarious, and really cares about the students (really helpful for grad school stuff). Definitely recommended

Dr. Ouimet is a young, passionate prof who keeps you engaged during lectures. There is definitely a fair amount of reading to do for the class but the material is really interesting, which makes it easier. Probably one of my favourite classes taken at university, would definitely recommend.

Her lectures are very interesting and engaging. She gives 2 midterms and a final, all multiple choice. They are definitely more tricky than the average class but if you know the all the material from the text book and her course lectures you will do well. She gives surprise in class assignments for participation marks. Overall, I would recommend!

She is totally down to earth and is very passionate about what she is teaching. She does however give very hard tests. I studied by far the most for this class and got C's on both midterms.  Midterms are 50% lecture material 50% textbook material so you basically have to know it all. VERY nice and helpful during office hours thought! Recommend her!
